article.headline: Fairfield 69, Niagara 59
article.story: LEWISTON, N.Y. (AP) -- DeWitt Maxwell tied a season high with 22 points and Fairfield extended its winning streak to five games with a 69-59 victory over Niagara Saturday. Thirteen Niagara turnovers led to 20 Fairfield points as the teams exchanged the lead eight times. Fairfield (14-8, 7-4 MAAC) fell behind by as many as eight points early on and trailed 33-30 at halftime. The Stags took the lead at 16:58 of the second half on Michael Bell's 3-pointer. Niagara (14-7, 8-4) pulled even twice more before Fairfield mounted a 9-3 run keyed by Kudjo Sogadzi's 3-pointer. Sogadzi finished with 16 points and six rebounds and hit 4 of 6 from the foul line down the stretch. Niagara converted just 7 of 19 attempts from the floor in the second half. Juan Mendez led Niagara with 17 points, 4 rebounds and 3 blocked shots. Tremmell Darden added 11 points and James Reaves 10. Bell and Tyquan Goode each scored 10 points for Fairfield while Rob Thomson grabbed 8 rebounds.
